headline: Midsummer
description: Wearing a wreath of flowers is part of the Swedish tradition around Midsummer. Except for a few protected species, most wild flowers can be picked as part of Sweden's right of public access.

headline: Midsummer celebration
description: Midsummer takes place in June and is a celebration of the summer solstice, the longest day of the year. It is one of the most celebrated holidays in Sweden. A maypole is created and raised during the day, which people gather around to dance and sing.

headline: National Day
description: Since 1983, Sweden has celebrated its National Day on June 6. This is the date on which Gustav Vasa was crowned king in 1523, and on which a new constitution was adopted in 1809.

headline: Skeppsbron
description: Skeppsbron runs from Slussen down past the Royal Castle. It is the Stockholms oldest dock and was Stockholms most important dock until late 1700's. The buildings along Skeppsbron where built and owned by merchants with the support of the crown to impress incomming visitors.

headline: Summer in Old Town
description: The Stockholm neighbourhood dates back to the 13th century, and consists of medieval alleyways, cobbled streets, and town squares. Stortorget is the oldest public square in Gamla Stan.

headline: The houseboat at Naturbyn
description: The houseboat at Naturbyn is situated in the quiet lake Eldan in Värmland.

headline: White moose
description: There are approximately 350,000 moose in Sweden but only a very few number of white moose. The whiteness is not a form of albinism but a form of genetic variation. White moose have brown eyes and are accepted as equals by their brown counterparts.

headline: Brown bear
description: The Scandinavian brown bear is a peaceful omnivore that mainly feeds on berries, ants, grass and herbs. Bears could once be found all over Sweden. In the late 1920s, the bear became a protected species, after almost becoming extinct. Today there are around 3300 bears in Sweden and they can mainly be found in the northwestern part of Sweden.

headline: City Hall
description: View over Riddarholmen and the tower of the City Hall in Stockholm.
